x4freetext: Research reactors CIRUS and APSARA
For short-lived fission products, nitrate solutions
of 229Th (~10 ug), 241Pu (~2 ug) and 245Cm (~1 ug)
sealed in polypropylene tubes were taken.
For long-lived fission products, electrodeposited
targets of 229Th (~100 ug), 241Pu (~25 ug), 245Cm
(~4 ug) and 252Cf (~3 ug) covered with 0.0025 cm thick
aluminum foils were taken.
80 cm**3 detector coupled to a 4K channel
analyzer in live time mode.
The resolution of the detector system was 2.0 keV at
1332.0 keV and dead time was always kept less than 10%.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The uncertainties shown on FCY values are
the propagated errors due to errors on cumulative
yields and mass chain yields where as the
uncertainties quoted in the independent yields are the
standard deviations of replicate measurements.
The gamma lines and the nuclear spectroscopic data
of different nuclides were taken from:
* E. Browne, R.B. Firestone, in: V.S. Shirley (Ed.),
Tables of Radioactive Isotopes, 1986.
* J.Blachot,Ch.Fiche, Ann.Phys.(Paris)6,3-218(1981).
compiled by Mr.Paresh Prajapati and
Dr. S. Mukherjee of The M.S.University of Baroda.
